Qiao Xiaochun, a professor at the Institute of Population Research at the University of Beijing, said that central government authorities recently discussed even more radical changes, such as allowing couples to have two children if one of the partners is a single child.
In July, Shanghai became the first Chinese city to launch an aggressive campaign to encourage births.
