Like the dream, psychosis opens the locks to a tide of ideas and fantasies from the deeper layers of consciousness.
The perception of reality in psychosis is centered on the subject, according to Professor Thomas Fuchs, Head of the Department of Psychiatry of the Heidelberg University Hospital (Allgemeine Psychiatry im Universitätsklinikum).
