Garage price in four stages
With the Auda-Taller tool, the company Audex guarantees that the user gets a quote in just four steps: identifying the vehicle, looking for the spare part, creating a quote and generating it.
Ease of use is an essential element of these systems, especially to convince older professionals who, to a greater or lesser extent, are reluctant to use new management techniques.
The database includes 1,034 vehicles, including 666 passenger vehicles, 109 off-road vehicles, 137 motorcycles, 78 vans and 44 trucks.
Of course, to use it, a computer and an Internet connection are necessary.
Once the model to be repaired has been identified with its chassis number, an actual graphic image of the model in question appears and the necessary part is selected.
The user can include variables such as labour price, increases or discounts, and then print out the quote to give it to the customer.
Auda Taller is not an estimation tool like AudaPlus, but a reference catalogue.
The main difference between these two systems is that the one for garages does not include estimated labour time.
